					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6270605#post-3862685</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6270605/scp-3361#post-3862685</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 05 Jul 2018 05:35:43 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>RockTeethMothEyes</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4022320</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Good, solid read/concept. Bathroom stall doodle that offers therapy is not something I was expecting.</p> <p>The only thing that I think I would like more of is the post-interview. Does Agent blackbox take some time off to spend with his son? Does he slack a little in his work ethic? I want to know if bathroom doodle's words have any effect on him.</p> <p>Even if I never get to know the answers to these questions, +1 for talking about feelings while pooping.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6270605#post-3858341</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6270605/scp-3361#post-3858341</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 02 Jul 2018 06:10:03 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>RJB_R</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1229263</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I'm going to neutral vote. While I agree the last line has a nice punch to it the preceding dialogue feels a little wooden. The description gets the job done, but the whole interview would have to be something really special for me to upvote given the minimalist setup and this doesn't quite deliver on that. It definitely has the potential to, that dialogue just needs to be ironed over to sound more human.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6270605#post-3857923</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6270605/scp-3361#post-3857923</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 01 Jul 2018 22:56:29 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Captain Kirby</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3440103</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Upvoted, because I was really expecting the conversation to end like three different times, playing more off the &quot;does this guy really think bathroom therapy works?&quot; joke that permeated throughout the interview. I felt that the monologues were a little too straight forward and preachy, but that was also probably part of the character.</p> <p>But that last line though. Goddamn. Made me take a bathroom stall drawing seriously.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
